<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=edge">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>Email Verification</title>
  <style>
    * {
      margin: 0;
      padding: 0;
      box-sizing: border-box;
    }

    p {
      font-size: 15px;
      color: #666;
      margin: 20px 0;
    }
  </style>
</head>

<body style="font-family:'Segoe UI', Tahoma, Geneva, Verdana, sans-serif">
  <div style="font-size: 15px; color: #666; background: #fff; max-width: 600px; margin: 12px auto;">
    <h2 style="background: #0270dd; padding: 20px; color: #fff; font-size: 24px; font-weight: 600;"> One Time Password </h2>
    <div style="padding: 20px; border: 1px solid rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.3);">
      <h3 style="color: #333; margin-bottom: 12px;">Hi <%= username %>, </h3>
      <p>To reset your <span style="color: #333;font-weight: 500;">Writee</span> account password, we just need to make sure this email address is yours.</p>
      <p>To verify your email address, please use the OTP code below:</p>
      <p style="color: #333; font-size: 20px; font-weight: bold; text-align: center;"><%= otp %></p>
      <p>If you didn't request this OTP, you can safely ignore this email. Someone else might have typed your email address by mistake.</p>
      <div style="color: #333;">
        <p style="margin-bottom: 8px; display: block;">Thanks,</p>
        <p style="color: #333;font-weight: 500; margin: 0; display: block;">Writee Team</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</body>

</html>